 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.3","title":"[audit][time] Clamp overdue timer_driver next_deadline to now","description":"TimerDriver::next_deadline() currently forwards the wheel's stale internal deadline even after the underlying clock has already advanced past it. That leaks an overdue absolute deadline to callers instead of reporting the timer as immediately due. Fix next_deadline to compare against the current clock time and clamp overdue deadlines to now, preserving None for no timers and the real future deadline otherwise. Add deterministic regression tests for both TimerDriver and TimerDriverHandle.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GoldBasin","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:49:01.453506616Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T01:58:07.151259356Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T01:58:07.143029768Z","close_reason":"Completed; src/time/driver.rs implementation landed, rch cargo check --lib passed, repo-wide cargo test/check/clippy remain blocked by unrelated kafka test imports, service/buffer clippy findings, and existing fmt drift in other lanes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","time","timers"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:49:01.453506616Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.30","title":"[audit][plan] Remove stdout writes from execute_plan_in_lab_core","description":"Audit child for src/plan/fixtures.rs. Remove direct stdout writes from execute_plan_in_lab_core in non-test library code, replace with structured tracing or silence, and add regression coverage so non-test plan fixture execution paths do not reintroduce println! calls.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:29:40.979833040Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:02:44.790338473Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:02:40.958094680Z","close_reason":"Completed: removed non-test stdout writes from execute_plan_in_lab_core, added regression coverage, and validated with rch check/clippy/focused test","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","plan"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.30","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:29:40.979833040Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2455,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.30","author":"WhiteCliff","text":"Validation update: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/plan/fixtures.rs passed. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/rch-whitecliff-plan-fixtures-check2 cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed remotely after underscore-fixing trace-only locals. rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/rch-whitecliff-plan-fixtures-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings also passed remotely. A focused rch lib test for non_test_plan_fixture_paths_do_not_print_directly is still in flight / wrapper-silent.","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:49:59Z"}]}
